It is the contractor's responsibility to maintain adequate sediment & erosion control during all phases of construction to the satisfaction of the Principal's representative and local authorities inclusive of any fees and charges.

All testing and certifications required by an approved geotechnical engineer, carried out in accordance with the project specifications and relevant Australian Standards. Including but not limited to Level 1 supervision on structural fill, compaction, wet density, CBR testing as required.

Removal of existing dwellings and structures, hardstand areas, stormwater structures, road pavements, wearing surface, kerbing and footpaths as detailed within the engineering documentation inclusive of removal of spoil material off site to an approved waste facility.

Dewatering and desilting of existing dams to facilitate the construction of earthworks and infrastructure. Item inclusive of all works required to dewater, excavate to a solid base and remove materials off site to approved wate facility, and replace material inclusive of geotechnical certification and associated testing in accordance with AS3798 including relative compaction testing carried out in accordance with AS1289. Inclusive of fish extraction and all fauna management.
